Subject: FEATURE: support for persistent flag in reaction-based LPN to SBML
Date: Thu, 27 Jan 2011 17:16:04 -0700
Cc: ZHEN ZHANG <zhen.zhang@utah.edu>
X-Mailer: Apple Mail (2.936)

When the persistent flag is true for a transition, t, with an  
exponential delay, r,  should convert it to a rule, reaction, and  
event as follows:

Rule:
t = piecewise(1, (*t & e) | (*t & t), 0)

Reaction:
reactant 	 t
product tp
rate law  r * t

Event:
trigger tp
pers    false
delay  0
assignments
    *t = 0
     t* = 1
     <A>


